about.summary: Wrapper around the 'SVDLIBC' library for (truncated) singular value decomposition of a sparse matrix. Currently, only sparse real matrices in Matrix package format are supported.

name: r-sparsesvd
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.1-4' %}

{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-sparsesvd
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  fn: sparsesvd_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/sparsesvd_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/sparsesvd/sparsesvd_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 55e92cb1654a345cc3209691268fc52d893d14660e9e5c4cb36d7351ca38c3f9

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1001
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{posix}}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{posix}}make
    - {{posix}}sed               # [win]
    - {{posix}}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-matrix
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{native}}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-matrix

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('sparsesvd')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('sparsesvd')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://tedlab.mit.edu/~dr/SVDLIBC/, http://wordspace.r-forge.r-project.org/
  license: BSD_3_clause
  summary: Wrapper around the 'SVDLIBC' library for (truncated) singular value decomposition
    of a sparse matrix. Currently, only sparse real matrices in Matrix package format
    are supported.
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
